SENATE BILL No. 284
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 36-8-29.1.
Synopsis: Law enforcement civilian oversight boards. Provides that
any type of law enforcement civilian oversight board or commission or
any other entity established by a county, municipality, or township to
provide civilian oversight over a law enforcement agency, excluding
merit boards and commissions, may operate only in an advisory
capacity to the applicable law enforcement agency and does not have
binding authority over the law enforcement agency.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Carrasco, Freeman
January 12, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Corrections and Criminal
Law.
2026 IN 284—LS 6984/DI 116

